e on the “Front” of the robot).</p>
<p>But also, the Yaw angles (turn inward) are backward. Yaw is right-handed with your thumb pointing up, so your left camera is yawed <em>negative</em> 35 degrees and the right is yawed positive 35.  This will definitely screw up the results.</p>
<p>So, to fix the code you posted earlier, I think it should be:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">Camera camera_Right{
            "1229_Camera",

            frc::Transform2d{
                units::meter_t{0.27},
                units::meter_t{-0.27},
                frc::Rotation2d(units::degree_t{35})
        }
};

Camera camera_Left{
            "1229_Camera_Left",

            frc::Transform2d{
                units::meter_t{0.27},
                units::meter_t{0.27},
                frc::Rotation2d(units::degree_t{-35})
        }
 };
</code></pre>
<p>That should get you close, but as you already noticed, since you have the cameras tilted, you really should be doing this in 3d all the way to the end, and then stripping it down to 2d.</p>
<p>You can use the example from JohnFogarty, or you can see our code here: <a href="https://github.com/ligerbots/ReefScape2025/blob/main/src/main/java/frc/robot/subsystems/AprilTagVision.java" class="inline-onebox" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">ReefScape2025/src/main/java/frc/robot/subsystems/AprilTagVision.java at main · ligerbots/ReefScape2025 · GitHub</a></p>
<p>One word of caution however: 3D rotations are a really pain to specify correctly. The exact way they are written, in particular, the order that the angles are applied makes a difference, and can be hard to debug. What we use for the camera Rotation3d is (Java, and using your numbers):</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">new Rotation3d(0.0, Math.toRadians(-10), 0).rotateBy(new Rotation3d(0, 0, Math.toRadians(-35))
</code></pre>
<p>So, pitch the camera <em>up</em> by 10 degrees (yes, a tilt up is a <em>negative</em> angle), followed by a yaw of 35 degrees. Don’t just put the yaw angle in the third argument.</p>
<p>Hope this helps and good luck. Happy to keep helping.</p>","post_number":13,"post_type":1,"posts_count":13,"updated_at":"2025-03-25T13:13:25.059Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":11,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":4,"reads":44,"readers_count":43,"score":28.8,"yours":false,"topic_id":496827,"topic_slug":"how-to-setup-two-angled-cameras-with-photonvision","display_username":"Paul Rensing","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://github.com/ligerbots/ReefScape2025/blob/main/src/main/java/frc/robot/subsystems/AprilTagVision.java","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"ReefScape2025/src/main/java/frc/robot/subsystems/AprilTagVision.java at main · ligerbots/ReefScape2025 · GitHub","clicks":4}],"read":true,"user_title":"","reply_to_user":{"id":50772,"username":"wildmustang4903","name":"","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/wildmustang4903/{size}/263428_2.png"},"bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":25118,"hidden":false,"trust_level":2,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"user_custom_fields":{"user_field_4":"FRC 2877 LigerBots Mentor"},"post_url":"/t/how-to-setup-two-angled-cameras-with-photonvision/496827/13","reactions":[],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":0,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null}],"stream":[3567718,3567742,3567752,3567765,3567766,3567767,3567770,3567776,3567874,3567899,3567901,3567905,3567923]},"timeline_lookup":[[1,132],[9,131]],"suggested_topics":[{"id":485354,"title":"PathPlanner Auto just goes back and forth with increasing speed